19:47.920 --> 19:50.389
of the old amusement park
from the original days there.

19:50.455 --> 19:51.890
And I think
that's the heartbeat.

19:51.957 --> 19:53.659
And when I go in there,
I turn into a nine-year-old.

19:53.725 --> 19:57.496
All right, now, these are the
old-time games where you can win

19:57.563 --> 19:59.565
a stuffed animal. All right,
how about this game over here?

19:59.631 --> 20:02.434
-Oh. I mean, come on.
-You can win a giant banana.

20:02.501 --> 20:04.503
Well, I always want
to hit the middle. Oh.

20:04.570 --> 20:07.205
-Just one. (laughs)
-Why-why can't I...?

20:07.272 --> 20:09.207
I mean, I'm two feet away.

20:09.274 --> 20:10.576
Oh! How about that?
How about that?

20:10.642 --> 20:12.978
-Huh? Come on now.
-How do you like me now?

20:13.045 --> 20:14.947
Okay, one last time.

20:15.013 --> 20:16.515
-Aw. (laughs)
-Here you go.

20:16.582 --> 20:18.617
I present you your first
Kennywood win right here.

20:18.684 --> 20:20.852
There you are.
Congratulations.

20:20.919 --> 20:22.955
-This is the Jack Rabbit?
-This is the Jack Rabbit,

20:23.021 --> 20:25.991
The big attraction on the Jack
Rabbit was it has a double dip.

20:26.058 --> 20:27.225
Sweet.
This is where we're going?

20:27.292 --> 20:29.595
-This is where we're going.
-Me, you and our blue banana.

20:29.661 --> 20:31.296
I wonder if they'll let us
take this on there with us.

20:31.363 --> 20:32.731
-Can we take him with us?
-BILLY: Can...?

20:32.798 --> 20:33.932
Hi. Can we put him
in the coaster with us?

20:33.999 --> 20:35.601
-Oh, we can?
-Yeah.
-All right.

20:35.667 --> 20:37.603
-He's gonna go with us.
-Oh, you're going
with us, buddy.

20:37.669 --> 20:39.605
-All right.
-That's it..

20:40.272 --> 20:42.007
-Okay.
-You ready? You ready?
-Uh, ready?

20:42.074 --> 20:43.775
-All right.
-All right. Let's go.

20:43.842 --> 20:46.278
-I'm nervous!
-(Billy laughs)

20:46.345 --> 20:47.279
NISCHELLE:
This is going to be good.

20:47.346 --> 20:49.247
The Jack Rabbit was amazing.

20:49.314 --> 20:50.582
How'd you talk me into this,

20:50.649 --> 20:52.017
-Billy Gardell?
-Ah...

20:52.084 --> 20:53.585
<i>BILLY: I got the same feeling</i>
<i>riding it that I did</i>

20:53.652 --> 20:54.953
when I was a kid,
so it was really a treat.

20:55.020 --> 20:56.655
All right,
there's the rollercoaster noise

20:56.722 --> 20:59.992
you wait for.
This is the anxiety, right?

21:00.058 --> 21:01.460
Nischelle, I think,
really enjoyed herself.

21:01.526 --> 21:02.761
-(screaming)
-Yeah!

21:02.828 --> 21:05.764
<i>And she's funny</i>
<i>because she's hysterical</i>

21:05.831 --> 21:06.865
on the roller coaster.

21:06.932 --> 21:07.933
Ready for one more?

21:08.000 --> 21:08.934
-Oh, my, this is enough.
-One more.

21:09.001 --> 21:11.303
-Ooh. Yeah.
-(yelling)

21:11.370 --> 21:13.805
But then, as soon as it's over,
she's ready to go again.

21:13.872 --> 21:15.841
-Awesome as the first time.
-Can we go again?

21:15.907 --> 21:17.609
<i>So, it was very fun</i>
<i>to get to turn her onto that</i>

21:17.676 --> 21:19.945
and go do that with her.
It was cool.

21:20.012 --> 21:22.547
And our banana made it safely.

21:22.614 --> 21:23.915
-The Banana!
-(Billy laughs)

21:23.982 --> 21:25.817
Best day ever!

21:30.656 --> 21:32.424
Oh, shoot.

21:32.491 --> 21:34.326
-Oh. (laughing)
-That's Kenny Kangaroo.

21:34.393 --> 21:37.062
Can't sneak up on people, Kenny.
What's wrong with you?

21:37.129 --> 21:39.464
-Perfect.
-Thank you so much, man.
-Thank you.

21:39.531 --> 21:40.866
<i>-BILLY: Appreciate it.</i>
<i>-Thank you, Kenny.</i>

21:43.402 --> 21:45.537
<i>NISCHELLE: Just when it seemed</i>
<i>like smooth sailing,</i>

21:45.604 --> 21:47.406
<i>Mother Nature decided</i>

21:47.472 --> 21:50.642
<i>to disrupt Billy and the team's</i>
<i>renovation schedule.</i>

21:50.709 --> 21:52.611
-This rain is a pain.
-Does nothing for construction

21:52.678 --> 21:54.446
and nothing for my hair.

21:54.513 --> 21:57.516
<i>NISCHELLE: And in an emotional</i>
<i>moment you won't want to miss,</i>

21:57.582 --> 21:59.818
<i>Billy takes Rob</i>
<i>to the local watering hole.</i>

21:59.885 --> 22:01.687
-Hey, Billy.
-Rocco! How are you, my brother?

22:01.753 --> 22:03.355
<i>NISCHELLE:</i>
<i>But Rob has a surprise</i>

22:03.422 --> 22:05.057
<i>to honor Billy's late father.</i>

22:05.123 --> 22:06.458
Ah, man.

22:14.466 --> 22:15.767
<i>NISCHELLE:</i>
<i>Billy Gardell has been back home</i>

22:15.834 --> 22:17.569
<i>in Pittsburgh almost two weeks,</i>

22:17.636 --> 22:19.004
<i>where he's surprising</i>
<i>Marianne O'Connell</i>

22:19.071 --> 22:20.605
<i>with a home renovation,</i>

22:20.672 --> 22:23.575
<i>including an entirely</i>
<i>transformed bedroom</i>

22:23.642 --> 22:26.578
<i>and an amazing</i>
<i>outdoor three-season room.</i>

22:27.345 --> 22:31.883
<i>SABRINA:</i>
<i>So far, everything has</i>
<i>been running pretty smoothly.</i>

22:31.950 --> 22:34.920
<i>We've done a lot of work inside,</i>
<i>spackling</i>

22:34.986 --> 22:38.724
<i>and sanding Marianne's bedroom</i>
<i>to get it ready for wallpaper.</i>

22:38.790 --> 22:41.359
<i>The three-season room</i>
<i>is really taking shape</i>

22:41.426 --> 22:45.363
<i>with new walls, electric,</i>
<i>and the stylish floor tile</i>

22:45.430 --> 22:48.967
<i>I think Marianne is going</i>
<i>to love. I'm so excited</i>

22:49.034 --> 22:51.603
<i>that my white picket fence</i>
<i>arrived and started going in.</i>

22:51.670 --> 22:52.871
<i>But Billy also wanted a safe way</i>

22:52.938 --> 22:54.940
<i>for Marianne</i>
<i>to get into the backyard.</i>

22:55.006 --> 22:57.542
<i>So we ripped down the old pavers</i>
<i>and built her</i>

22:57.609 --> 23:02.614
<i>a new wider path which we topped</i>
<i>with beautiful bluestone pavers.</i>

23:06.485 --> 23:09.821
<i>It has been a lot of hard work,</i>
<i>but we made it to day nine, and</i>

23:09.888 --> 23:11.423
<i>the rain has made</i>
<i>another appearance.</i>

23:11.490 --> 23:13.058
<i>But that's not going to stop us</i>

23:13.125 --> 23:15.460
<i>from finishing off the patio.</i>

23:15.527 --> 23:16.962
-What else do you need?
-Just a two-foot level,

23:17.028 --> 23:18.296
and then, um,

23:18.363 --> 23:20.499
-the other stones
are right over there.
-More of the pavers.

23:20.565 --> 23:21.833
-Thank you.
-(sighs)

23:21.900 --> 23:23.702
Yeah, this rain is a pain
because...

23:23.769 --> 23:26.705
It does nothing for construction
and nothing for my hair.

23:26.772 --> 23:28.640
Well, I don't know
about your hair,

23:28.707 --> 23:31.176
but it's definitely
causing a problem back here,

23:31.243 --> 23:34.146
and we got a lot
to do before we finish.

23:34.212 --> 23:35.514
What do you think so far?

23:35.580 --> 23:36.982
-It looks great.
-Yeah?

23:37.048 --> 23:39.451
This is such an improvement
from what it looked like before!

23:39.518 --> 23:40.886
I know. I know, and

23:40.952 --> 23:43.088
with this retaining wall
coming out further,

23:43.155 --> 23:45.023
they're not going to have those
water issues inside the house.

23:45.090 --> 23:46.725
It's so amazing.

23:46.792 --> 23:48.493
-Yeah, so...
-What an upgrade.

23:48.560 --> 23:51.730
No doubt. A couple more here,
and we'll be good.

23:51.797 --> 23:53.732
<i>SABRINA:</i>
<i>I think Marianne is really going</i>

23:53.799 --> 23:55.567
<i>to love this stonework.</i>

23:55.634 --> 23:58.603
-Rain is not going to stop us.
-(laughs) No doubt.

23:58.670 --> 24:01.006
<i>SABRINA:</i>
<i>It looks great, and it's going</i>
<i>to last a long time,</i>

24:01.072 --> 24:02.440
so I'm super excited
to get it done.

24:04.242 --> 24:06.178
Sabrina, that's not how
we set a stone.

24:06.244 --> 24:09.080
<i>-SABRINA: I got dirty. (laughs)</i>
<i>-ROB: (laughs) Horrible.</i>

24:10.182 --> 24:11.783
<i>ROB:</i>
<i>This morning,</i>

24:11.850 --> 24:14.653
<i>we got the windows installed</i>
<i>in the three-season room.</i>

24:14.719 --> 24:18.056
And just in time for--
you guessed it-- more rain.

24:18.123 --> 24:20.759
Hey, Dan, I need this one
67 and three quarters.

24:20.826 --> 24:22.794
-All right. Perfect.
-Okay.

24:22.861 --> 24:23.795
<i>ROB:</i>
<i>So we switched it up</i>
<i>and finished</i>

24:23.862 --> 24:25.897
<i>all the trim work inside.</i>

24:25.964 --> 24:27.899
<i>And now</i>
<i>that it's cleared up a bit,</i>

24:27.966 --> 24:30.068
Billy and I are going
to finish off the new gutter.

24:30.135 --> 24:31.903
Can you hand me that last
12-foot section of downspout?

24:31.970 --> 24:33.772
BILLY:
Yes, sir, I can.

24:33.839 --> 24:35.040
-Okay.
-Hey, man, thanks a lot

24:35.106 --> 24:36.474
for going the extra mile

24:36.541 --> 24:38.176
and finding that
and fixing this.

24:38.243 --> 24:39.678
-Yeah, no problem.
-Really appreciate it.

24:39.744 --> 24:41.179
This will divert the water,
and then,

24:41.246 --> 24:43.515
we'll just put the 90 on the end

24:43.582 --> 24:46.685
-and drop it right in.
-All right. You got it.

24:46.751 --> 24:48.186
-It goes right...
-Here we go.

24:48.253 --> 24:50.488
-All right.
-Set it up.

24:50.555 --> 24:52.757
-All right.
-There you go.
And just slide it

24:52.824 --> 24:54.526
right down and in.
That will take the water

24:54.593 --> 24:57.529
right into this gutter,
run down that way.

24:57.596 --> 24:58.897
Solves that whole problem.

24:58.964 --> 25:00.198
-Thank you, Rob.
-All right, brother.

25:00.265 --> 25:01.833
It's hard not
to like you even though

25:01.900 --> 25:03.034
you're a Patriots fan.
You know that?

25:03.101 --> 25:04.970
If I was a decent guy,
I'd reciprocate

25:05.036 --> 25:08.206
about the Steelers,
but I got to stay me, Billy.

25:08.273 --> 25:09.941
-I understand, Rob. I respect.
-I hear you.

25:10.008 --> 25:11.810
<i>ROB:</i>
<i>You know,</i>
<i>I give Billy a hard time,</i>

25:11.877 --> 25:13.778
but Billy's a good guy.

25:13.845 --> 25:15.547
-That way, Rob,
away from the roof.
-Okay.

25:15.614 --> 25:17.849
-All right. Sounds good.
-(laughs)

25:21.720 --> 25:24.089
So these slide down. They're a
little tricky. We got to kind of

25:24.155 --> 25:26.224
work together.
So there's four on that side

25:26.291 --> 25:27.959
-I installed there.
-Okay.

25:28.026 --> 25:29.661
So let me get this side in.

25:29.728 --> 25:31.730
In. There we go.

25:31.796 --> 25:33.231
-BILLY: There you go.
Right on the money.
-Okay.

25:33.298 --> 25:36.668
So we'll just kind of finagle
the pole a little bit.

25:37.335 --> 25:39.271
-That's actually really easy.
-That's 'cause

25:39.337 --> 25:41.573
-I already did all the hard work
installing that.
-What?

25:41.640 --> 25:42.741
-Oh, oh, oh.
-I was gonna say, it's easy

25:42.807 --> 25:44.709
when Rob does all the work,
prep work,

25:44.776 --> 25:45.744
-first.
-Right there.

25:45.810 --> 25:48.146
Just bring one end in first.
Down, down, down.

25:48.213 --> 25:50.148
-All right.
-Right there.

25:50.215 --> 25:52.083
There it is.

25:52.150 --> 25:54.119
-BILLY: There we go.
-Perfect. Last one.

25:54.185 --> 25:55.687
How about...? Wait.
When we finish,

25:55.754 --> 25:56.988
how am I going to get
to the other side?

25:57.055 --> 25:58.156
-Well, that's why...
-Now's your chance.

25:58.223 --> 26:00.592
If you want to get on the other
side, now's your chance.

26:00.659 --> 26:01.927
Rob said to put you
on that side while we're...

26:01.993 --> 26:03.328
-I know.
-No, I'm just...

26:03.395 --> 26:04.796
Was this my end?

26:04.863 --> 26:06.331
-(laughs)
-Billy, if we... if we hurry,

26:06.398 --> 26:08.934
we can keep her out here.

26:09.000 --> 26:10.302
-There it is.
-Bada bing.

26:10.368 --> 26:11.937
Yeah, that's it.

26:12.003 --> 26:14.806
-All right, Sabrina,
good seeing you.
-Sabrina.

26:14.873 --> 26:17.142
-I'm fenced out.
-Right on.
-Let me get the gate for you.

26:17.208 --> 26:19.611
-Thank you, sir.
-You're welcome.

26:19.678 --> 26:21.079
-BILLY: Perfect.
-All right.

26:21.146 --> 26:22.647
-How's that?
-What do you think, Billy?
-Perfect.

26:22.714 --> 26:24.983
This is awesome
and unbelievable.

26:25.050 --> 26:27.185
-She is going to love this.
It's so storybook.
-Come on.

26:27.252 --> 26:28.353
SABRINA: This is...
this is such an upgrade

26:28.420 --> 26:29.955
from the chain-link fence.

26:30.021 --> 26:31.690
-I love everything you've done.
-ROB: Yeah. Thank you.

26:31.756 --> 26:33.858
You know, with Billy
and Sabrina both helping,

26:33.925 --> 26:35.694
not only are we going
to get done a lot faster,

26:35.760 --> 26:37.262
but they made it a lot of fun.

26:37.329 --> 26:41.967
This will, uh,
at least give a little bit

26:42.033 --> 26:43.601
of extra support
going up these stairs for her.

26:43.668 --> 26:44.936
Yeah. No, absolutely.

26:45.003 --> 26:46.805
Boston Rob has been
a pleasure to work with,

26:46.871 --> 26:48.707
and you can really see the pride
he takes in his work.

26:48.773 --> 26:50.275
He's just a good,
down-to-earth guy.

26:50.342 --> 26:52.143
I want to take you to my old
neighborhood and buy you a beer.

26:52.210 --> 26:53.845
-We're finally going
to go to Rocco's?
-I'm...

26:53.912 --> 26:55.280
I'm taking you to Rocco's.
That's right.

26:55.347 --> 26:58.149
I've been hearing about Rocco
for the last two weeks.

26:58.216 --> 26:59.851
This is the moment
I've been waiting for.

26:59.918 --> 27:02.687
So I'm going to have my guys
finish up the railing.

27:02.754 --> 27:04.155
-Ready for some suds?
-Let's do it.

27:04.222 --> 27:05.890
You're going to wear that hat?

27:05.957 --> 27:07.359
I mean, Billy,
this goes everywhere with me.

27:07.425 --> 27:10.328
-Come on. (laughs)
-All right, man. I warned you.

27:11.496 --> 27:14.699
BILLY:
Now I want to say a proper
blue-collar thank you,

27:14.766 --> 27:15.834
and I can't think
of a better way to do that

27:15.900 --> 27:17.168
than the local bar

27:17.235 --> 27:18.837
that literally was the place

27:18.903 --> 27:20.338
that we grew up around,
you know?

27:20.405 --> 27:21.906
-I appreciate it, man.
-And you'll love

27:21.973 --> 27:23.408
this guy, too, man.

27:23.475 --> 27:25.043
You'll love Auggie Rocco.
He's a classic.

27:25.110 --> 27:27.412
<i>Rocco's Tavern is</i>
<i>a neighborhood institution.</i>

27:27.479 --> 27:30.315
You don't see those places
too much anymore, you know?

27:30.382 --> 27:32.817
<i>Rocco, who owns the place,</i>
<i>I love him to death.</i>

27:32.884 --> 27:35.887
<i>It's been a family-run bar</i>
<i>for over 75 years.</i>

27:35.954 --> 27:37.689
<i>My father used to go there,</i>

27:37.756 --> 27:39.924
<i>and, you know,</i>
<i>he had his own chair there, and</i>

27:39.991 --> 27:42.260
it's just very much the
neighborhood gathering joint.

27:42.327 --> 27:44.662
I'm gonna take you
through my alley.

27:44.729 --> 27:46.898
-Okay.
-'Cause I grew up...
I grew up in an alley.

27:46.965 --> 27:48.933
We would always get six
or seven of us,

27:49.000 --> 27:50.935
and then we'd get a good
Wiffle Ball game going.

27:51.002 --> 27:52.804
<i>-ROB: Yeah.</i>
<i>-And what we would do is,</i>

27:52.871 --> 27:55.440
<i>we would mark these yards.</i>
<i>Like,</i>

27:55.507 --> 27:57.208
if you hit it in that yard,
that was a single

27:57.275 --> 27:59.944
'cause the guy would let us
go get the ball.

28:00.011 --> 28:02.180
There's always one guy,
if you hit it in his yard,

28:02.247 --> 28:03.815
you're gonna get killed if you
don't get it out fast enough.

28:03.882 --> 28:05.683
-This is him.
-This is him.

28:05.750 --> 28:07.952
-This is the guy.
-What was his name?
Tell me his name.

28:08.019 --> 28:10.955
-Mr. Scanlon.
-Mr. Scanlon.

28:11.022 --> 28:12.090
Aah, we hated him.

28:12.891 --> 28:14.459
-ROB: And this is it.
-When you were underage,

28:14.526 --> 28:16.461
-this is what you aspired to.
-Yup.

28:16.528 --> 28:17.896
BILLY:
To be able to go have a beer

28:17.962 --> 28:19.230
with the guys at Rocco's,

28:19.297 --> 28:20.432
and I'm happy
to bring you in here.

28:20.498 --> 28:22.233
-Hey, Billy.
-Rocco! How are you, my brother?

28:22.300 --> 28:24.169
Give me a hug, kiddo.

28:24.235 --> 28:26.104
-Good to see you, baby.
Good to see you.
-How are you?

28:26.171 --> 28:28.073
-Is this your friend?
-This is Boston Rob.

28:28.139 --> 28:30.241
This is a Pittsburgh bar. You're
gonna have to take your hat off.

28:30.308 --> 28:32.477
Listen, this comes with me
everywhere I go.

28:32.544 --> 28:34.145
-I read a lot about you.
-This man's done a lot of work.

28:34.212 --> 28:36.014
We got to give him a pass.

28:36.081 --> 28:38.116
<i>BILLY:</i>
<i>Auggie has a special place</i>
<i>in my heart</i>

28:38.183 --> 28:40.852
<i>because he was such dear friends</i>
<i>with my father.</i>

28:40.919 --> 28:42.120
-And this was his seat.
-This was his seat, and...

28:42.187 --> 28:43.121
That was his seat, and there was

28:43.188 --> 28:44.389
no one allowed in that seat.

28:44.456 --> 28:46.057
That's right. And what
if somebody was in here?

28:46.124 --> 28:48.193
-Oh, he's gone.
-That's right.

28:48.259 --> 28:50.495
-You got... Some box seats, man.
-Right out of there.

28:50.562 --> 28:53.331
And one of the lovely things
he did when my dad passed, man,

28:53.398 --> 28:55.133
they put a picture
of him here,

28:55.200 --> 28:57.869
-and everybody came in
and celebrated my father.
-ROB: Yeah.

28:57.936 --> 29:00.138
It's hard not to get choked up
thinking about it.

29:00.205 --> 29:02.273
I could see him
coming through the door, yeah.

29:02.340 --> 29:04.142
-ROB: When you told me
about Auggie...
-Right.

29:04.209 --> 29:06.111
...I actually called him, and

29:06.177 --> 29:08.146
-we set a little something up.
-Oh, you did?

29:08.213 --> 29:11.282
This is something that we wanted
to do to commemorate

29:11.349 --> 29:14.252
your dad and all the time
he spent here.

29:14.319 --> 29:17.122
And this is going
to stay right here in his spot.

29:17.188 --> 29:19.424
-Ah, come on.
-We're going
to put it here permanently.

29:19.491 --> 29:20.425
Well, thank you.

29:20.492 --> 29:21.526
<i>Rob and Auggie</i>

29:21.593 --> 29:24.496
found a-a circular plaque
that said,

29:24.562 --> 29:29.167
<i>uh, "This seat dedicated</i>
<i>to William 'Corky' Gardell,</i>

29:29.234 --> 29:32.103
<i>a loyal friend and patron."</i>

